headline: Homebuilders Fear Profit Margins Will Shrink
summary: An exchange-traded fund tracking companies in the home construction industry was dropping in after-hours trading.  Two large builders, D.R. Horton and Lennar, were down 2.1% and 2.9%, respectively, after ending the day higher.
